\b Black to Play.\b0
When white invades the corner at 1, black 2 blocks in the right direction.

When there a black stone like \'a1\'e3, you should play like this in order to place an emphasis on developing this side.

After white 3 and black 4 are exchanged, it might look a little strange for white to extend with 5.

How can black respond to this move?
